/*! \mainpage Amesos to %Thyra Linear Solver Adapters

This doxygen collection documents a small amount of code that wraps
<tt>Amesos_BaseSolver</tt> objects to implement the
<tt>Thyra::LinearOpWithSolveBase</tt> and
<tt>Thyra::LinearOpWithSolveFactoryBase</tt> interfaces.  The subclass
<tt>Thyra::AmesosLinearOpWithSolveFactory</tt> should be used by clients to
manage the creation of <tt>Thyra::LinearOpWithSolveBase</tt> objects from
<tt>Thyra::EpetraLinearOpBase</tt> objects.

See \ref single_amesos_thyra_adapters_testing_prg_grp "this testing program"
for how these adapters are used to take an <tt>Epetra_CrsMatrix</tt> and us it
to create these linear solver objects.

<ul>

<li> \ref Amesos_Thyra_adapters_grp : Documents the basic wrapper code
for turning Epetra objects into %Thyra objects.

<li> \ref Amesos_Thyra_examples_grp : Gives some examples of the use of
the Epetra to Thyra adapter code.

</ul>

*/

/** \defgroup Amesos_Thyra_adapters_grp Amesos to Thyra Linear Solver Adapter Code

\section Amesos_Thyra_adapters_classes_sec Classes

<ul>

<li><tt>Thyra::AmesosLinearOpWithSolveFactory</tt> : A general concrete
implementation of the <tt>Thyra::LinearOpWithSolveFactoryBase</tt> interface
that creates <tt>Thyra::AmesosLinearOpWithSolve</tt> objects.

<li><tt>Thyra::AmesosLinearOpWithSolve</tt> : A very general concrete
implementation of the <tt>Thyra::LinearOpWithSolveBase</tt> interface.
Clients should not create these objects directly but instead should use
<tt>Thyra::AmesosLinearOpWithSolveFactory</tt> for that purpose.

</ul>

\section Amesos_Thyra_examples_sec Examples

<ul>
<li> \ref Amesos_Thyra_examples_grp
</ul>

*/

